page.title: 11TREFULLOCK MOOR
page.content: This settlement has grown over the last 25 years, on moorland of little economic value into a rather sprawling and from the outside an untidy settlement. In 1940 the nucleus was there in the form of 2 old railway carriage dwellings. The variety of moveable homes is great, including old caravans,chalets,old vans and coaches in various states of repair. Some have wooden extensions. Often the plots are enclosed by poor fences of a mixture of collected materials. A few of the plots were empty. Several animals were kept as pets including ponies, dogs, cats and birds. Some of the gardens revealed a pride of possession as plants had been introduced. In one garden there was a young eucalypt, in another a palm and bamboo. However with the predominance of old vehicles the area would not appeal to all.
